<h2>View</h2>
<p>Foundation for all show/hide/render patterns. Provides a shared engine and specialized blocks that higher-level components (Tabs, Router, Accordion) build on.</p>

<p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-text-muted);">
  <strong>Terminology:</strong> See <a href="/semantics/">Semantics & Glossary</a> for terms like <a href="/semantics/#term-view">view</a>, <a href="/semantics/#term-hidden-visible">hidden/visible</a>, and <a href="/semantics/#term-commandfor-command">commandfor/command</a>.
</p>

<h3>Architecture</h3>
<p>View separates two concerns:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>ViewEngine</strong> (shared core): How to hide/show &mdash; hidden modes, toggle events, transitions, exclusive groups</li>
  <li><strong>Blocks</strong> (specialized): When/whether to hide/show &mdash; each block solves a different DOM-presence scenario</li>
</ul>
<p>Higher-level components don't reimplement show/hide mechanics. They pick the View block that fits their DOM model, or use the engine directly.</p>

<h3>The Core Question: What Exists in the DOM?</h3>
<p>The right block depends on what should be in the DOM when content is <strong>not active</strong>:</p>

<table>
  <tr>
    <th>DOM When Inactive</th>
    <th>Block</th>
    <th>Type</th>
    <th>When to Use</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Full element + content, just hidden</td>
    <td><a href="#view-behavior">ViewBehavior</a></td>
    <td>Behavior</td>
    <td>Tabs, accordion, disclosure, toggling existing content</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Element exists, visibility bound to expression</td>
    <td><a href="#view-show">ViewShowBehavior</a></td>
    <td>Behavior</td>
    <td>Reactive show/hide, dropdowns, conditional UI</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Nothing &mdash; DOM stamped on condition, destroyed when false</td>
    <td><a href="#view-if">ViewIfDirective</a></td>
    <td>Directive</td>
    <td>Login gates, feature flags, expensive components</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Nothing &mdash; one branch stamped at a time from multiple options</td>
    <td><a href="#view-switch">ViewSwitchDirective</a></td>
    <td>Directive</td>
    <td>Multi-step wizards, state-dependent UI, mode switching</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<h4>Decision Guide</h4>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Does the content always exist in your HTML?</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>Yes &rarr; Is it toggled by commands/triggers or by an expression?
        <ul>
          <li>Commands (buttons, Invoker Commands) &rarr; <strong>ViewBehavior</strong></li>
          <li>Expression/state &rarr; <strong>ViewShowBehavior</strong></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>No, it should only exist when a condition is met &rarr;
        <ul>
          <li>Binary (true/false) &rarr; <strong>ViewIfDirective</strong></li>
          <li>Multiple branches &rarr; <strong>ViewSwitchDirective</strong></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>Do you need accessibility for hidden content?</strong>
    <ul>
      <li><code>hidden="until-found"</code> (Ctrl+F finds it) &rarr; use a Behavior (content must be in DOM)</li>
      <li><code>content-visibility: hidden</code> (stays in a11y tree) &rarr; use a Behavior</li>
      <li>No trace when inactive &rarr; use a Directive</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>Should state survive hide/show cycles?</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>Behaviors preserve state naturally (element stays in DOM)</li>
      <li>Directives destroy state by default, use <code>view:keep-alive</code> to cache</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

